es.utils.mapper.factory

Class CollectionFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.utils.mapper.factory.CollectionFactory

  • public class CollectionFactory
extends Object
    This class lets you instantiate a collection based on destination class type. The destination class type should be a concrete class (e.g. subclasses of Collection), otherwise an exception is thrown. If the destination class type is an array, an ArrayList is created.
    Author:
    eschoysman

        public static <IN,OUT> Collection<OUT> create(Class<? extends Collection> inputCollectionType,
                                              Class<? extends Collection> collectionType)
        This method instantiate a new collection based on collectionType.
        Type Parameters:
        IN - the type of the objects in the origin collection
        OUT - the type of the objects in the destination collection
        Parameters:

        collectionType - the class of input. It must extend Collection.
        Returns:
        a new instance of collectionType.
